RACE.FOOTNOTES: NATURAL STAR was nestled on the rail tracking the front two horses in the beginning, was checked mildly on the fence with three furlongs to go, regrouped quickly inside waiting to pounce at the quarter pole, angled outside for clear run in the three path in mid stretch and was full of run late drawing away at the wire. BANKINGONAMIRACLE chased the frontrunner two wide down the backside, edged closer to hound the pacesetter outside on the turn, loomed the threat in the four path at the top of the lane, battled between rivals at the sixteenth pole but was outfinished by the winner in deep stretch. MYRA'S BOY was away a bit slow to begin, stalked near the rear in the early going, roused three wide keeping pace with the leaders on the turn to be in with a chance behind foes turning for home and found his best stride late to close in for third nearing the wire. KITTY'SSPEEDYSTARR took this field down the backstretch dictating terms up front, had a narrow advantage running throughout the turn, was headed outside at the top of the lane, shifted inwards under the drive to the rail at the furlong marker and could not find more late to quicken with the top two foes nearing the wire. COMPUTER HACKER settled three deep in midpack down the backside, offered a brief move three wide at the three furlong marker, swung out to the five path widest for the stretch drive but stalled in the final furlong. DUBAWI BULL hesitated at the the break to trail the field down the back straight, could not recover enough to reach contention running throughout the turn and was not involved in the stretch drive due to the compromised beginning.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPRING MOUNTAIN hounded the pace outside in the beginning, continued to force the issue running on the turn, bid for the lead in the four path turning for home, took over control in mid stretch, surrendered the lead at the sixteenth pole and dug back in when lightly bumped nearing the wire to surge for the win at the finish line. BONGINO was in a good spot tucked in on the rail watching the contesting pair down the backside, waited on the fence to pounce on the leaders through the turn, looked for a path at the top of the stretch, had clear run in the three path with three sixteenths remaining, poked his head in front with a sixteenth to go, drifted out slightly driving to the wire late and was outgamed by the resurging winner at the finish. EXULT travelled in midpack on the rail in the early stages, stalked inside in the third flight through the turn, waited behind a wall of runners at the top of the lane, angled inwards in upper stretch to the rail for clear run and showed late energy to close in and capture third crossing the line. NEWPORT AGENT had a good position outside horses in the second flight down the backstretch, kept a close eye on the contesting pair throughout the turn, posed a serious threat in the five path straightening out for the stretch drive and evened out in the final furlong for a minor share. TOURIST'S DREAM set the fractions down the backstretch, continued up front with a slim advantage on the turn, was clinging to the lead in the three path turning for home, battled until the eighth pole, could not find another gear late and faded in deep stretch. INFAMOUS COVERT settling near the back three deep outside foes down the back straight, advanced three wide making a move at the three furlong marker, swung out widest to the six path to be in the hunt for the stretch run and levelled off in the final furlong. BOKERMIN was unhurried to trail the field down the backside, saved ground seeing the field running on the turn and when roused straightening out for the drive could not get involved in the late stages of the race. COPINSAY stalked between foes in the two path near the back in the early going, made little impression through the turn and could not make a presence in the stretch run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JMR SPEEDY ESCAPE took control from the onset, opened up on the chasing rival through the turn, had a comfortable lead straightening out for the drive and began to get leg weary late but had enough left to hold for the win at the wire. YODDHA tracked on the fence in the early going, settled on the rail in midfield alone running through the turn, shifted outside gaining momentum at the quarter pole making a strong move and finished up on the wrong lead to the wire gaining steadily with every stride but just missed in the end. DIXIE'S FLATTER travelled near the rear on the rail in the beginning, saved ground running on the turn making some progress on rivals, slipped up the fence in upper stretch, split foes in the three path in the final eighth and closed in to capture third at the wire. SERENADE AT SEA tracked sitting behind the leader down the back straight, was nudged for more run midturn to be in the hunt in the three path between foes in upper stretch and was one paced late holding for a small share in the end. SMOKIN HOLIDAY tracked three deep in the early stages, offered a brief run two wide at the three eighths pole to take closer order running on the turn, was in the mix in the three path at the top of the lane but stalled when in tight between foes at the furlong marker. COMMANDER AT SEA prompted the pace two wide down the backstretch, chased the frontrunning winner in vain throughout the far turn and weakened on the fence in upper stretch. NO MORE SALT was bumped inside at the start to trail down the back straight, regrouped to catch up to the field midway on the turn but could not find more to be a factor driving to the finish. HOLIDAY IN CHILE broke out at the stretch, stalked near the rear down the backside, was roused with five sixteenths to go making little progress and showed little interest in the stretch drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HANK OLLIE stalked just off the leaders mid-pack outside rivals, went four wide on the turn, angled out six wide leaving that bend and put to urging, struck the lead near the furlong grounds while drifting in, continued to drift in a bit and held sway to prevail. GUARD OF HONOUR attended the early pace inside, took the lead still in hand after the opening quarter, was clear into the turn, led them into upper stretch coming off the rail, was overtaken slightly in mid-stretch, fought on but was outfinished. QUIET VISTA got away well, was forwardly-positioned early, stalked the runner-up from outside through the turn three deep, kept on. MAGNIFICENT MARIO broke well and head the early lead briefly, eased back and tucked in behind stalking from about the two path just off the leading pair into the turn, moved out a bit early on that bend then angled out further midway, came into upper stretch five wide and in range, ran on evenly. FLAWLESS RULER settled off the pace going three wide through the turn, came out six wide in the stretch, put forth good late effort but was too little too late. SHAMROCK AMBASADOR was well-placed mid-pack tracking from inside, saved ground on the turn, ran on evenly. CELENTANO broke a step slowly, was a bit rank running up on heels, checked sharply and bumped a rival lightly then steadied again abruptly, settled into stride before making a rapid middle-move between runners from the seven-sixteenths to the top of the stretch, was within range at that juncture seeking room in behind runners, was guided out for clear sailing but lacked the needed late kick. GREYSTONE was lightly bumped in the early going, settled at the back, switched out and was niggled along at the half, advanced outside foes on the turn five then six wide, drew to within striking distance coming seven wide to the top of the stretch but offered no late bid. AMAZON FORESTER hopped at the start, was forced out and slow into stride, raced five wide into the turn, dropped back and faded. LE GRAND GARCON was a bit reluctant to load, raced between runners into the turn while at the back, tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAILOR'S PASSION settled on the rail near the back in the early stages, advanced smartly up the fence at the half, waited patiently inside on the far turn ready to fire, rallied up the fence in upper stretch and held on prevailing in a photo for the win. STOLEN MONEY pulled the rider to the lead in the first turn, maintained a slim advantage down the back straight, was collared on each side by foes in upper stretch, surrendered the lead at the sixteenth pole and gamely fought back to just lose the nod in a tight finish. SUNRISE DRIVE travelled outside in midpack in the second flight down the backside, rallied three wide outside runners midpoint on the final turn, loomed in the six path at the top of the lane, and stalled while not switching leads in the final furlong but still ran on the be a solid third at the wire. COLEYVILLE was allowed to settle trailing inside in the early stages, closed in on a tightly bunched pack seeing the field at the half, began to pick up runners midway on the far turn inside, looked for a seam at the top of the stretch and finished up willingly through the lane for a small piece of the prize. ROCKET JOE COPPER was under a tight hold watching the engaging pair into the first turn, fought the restraining rider early down the backside, relaxed kindly by the half mile marker, was roused three furlongs from home in the three path to be in the hunt in the five path straightening out for the drive but lacked a closing response in mid stretch. RELIABILITY was hustled to the lead angling inwards into the first turn, pressed the pace outside down the backstretch, was still in the thick of things in the four path turning for home but could not offer more and tired in the final furlong. IPSUM GRATUS travelled two wide near the back in the beginning, made little progress running down the backside, could not keep up with others quickening on the final turn and could not be a factor driving to the finish.
